abstract: Moldova's Parliament ousts pro-European Union Prime Min Valeriu Strelet and his cabinet after less than three months in office; capital of Chisinau has been scene of month-long protests against government corruption.
lead_paragraph: Sixty-five of the chamber’s 101 lawmakers voted to dismiss the government of Prime Minister Valeriu Strelet, who has held the post since July, and his cabinet.

headline.main: Moldova Parliament Dismisses Government Amid Bank Scandal
headline.print_headline: World Briefing | Europe; Moldova: Bank Scandal Leads to Ouster of Prime Minister After 3 Months
